version: 0.3.1
date-released: "2026-04-01"
abstract: >-
  AI-Native Notation (ANN) is a structured communication protocol for
  cross-architecture AI state transfer. Nine core block types and seven
  transfer protocol blocks encode processing instructions, epistemic
  status, and reasoning chains in a format that LLM architectures adopt
  spontaneously. Validated across six architectures (Claude, Gemini,
  ChatGPT, DeepSeek, Grok, MiniMax) with 89/90 cross-architecture
  accuracy.
